HEADWORD: Giglet
<hw>Gig"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Icel. <ets>gikkr</ets> a pert, rude
person, Dan. <ets>giek</ets> a fool, silly man, AS. <ets>gagol</ets>,
<ets>g⟦ae⟧gl</ets>, lascivious, wanton, MHG. <ets>gogel</ets> wanton,
<ets>giege</ets> fool, and E. <ets>gig</ets> a wanton person.]</ety>
<def>A wanton; a lascivious or light, giddy girl.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>giglet</qex> is willful, and is running upon her
fate.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Giglot</ent>⟦br⟧
